  "prompt": "How can I change the \"Ok Google\" phrase to something else in a Nexus 6?",
  "response": "On a Nexus 6, you can customize the \"Ok Google\" voice command by following these steps:\n\n1. Go to Settings\n2. Tap \"Voice\"\n3. Select \"Voice Match\"\n4. Toggle \"Ok Google\" detection on\n5. You'll see an option to \"Train voice model\" where you can re-record your launch phrase\n\nHowever, the Nexus 6 is somewhat limited in completely changing the exact phrase. The default is still \"Ok Google\" but you can customize how sensitively it responds to your voice.\n\nFor more custom wake phrases, some users recommend third-party apps like \"AlwaysListen\" from the Google Play Store, which offer more flexible voice command options. But always be cautious with third-party apps and check reviews and permissions.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these steps?",
